From 85458c2eca24328e702bffd817ae3f3be6448ff5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Paul Swenson <pdscomp@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 16:03:35 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] video: cc2: add ST77922 DSI panel and host driver

Add the Allwinner MIPI-DSI host controller, Sitronix ST77922
panel driver, TCON-TOP mux, and R528 display clock gates so
the Elegoo Centauri Carbon 2 U-Boot can drive the MIPI-DSI
panel and hand off a simple-framebuffer node to Linux.

Guard the DSI-specific additions in sunxi_lcd.c with
CONFIG_VIDEO_SUNXI_MIPI_DSI so the shared R528 display code
remains safe for the Carbon 1 parallel-RGB build.

Signed-off-by: Paul Swenson <pdscomp@gmail.com>
